er-genius-sports-as-commercial-partner-explained%2Farticleshow%2F129864373.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Genius%20Sports%20and%20FanCode%20have%20submitted%20bids%20for%20Indian%20Super%20League%20(ISL)%20and%20Federation%20Cup%20commercial%20rights%2C%20with%20Genius%20Sports%20offering%20a%20significantly%20higher%20amount.%20While%20the%20All%20India%20Football%20Federation%20(AIFF)%20favours%20Genius%20Sports'%20larger%20upfront%20offer%2C%20ISL%20clubs%20prefer%20FanCode's%20more%20sustainable%20financial%20structure%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20divergence%20in%20opinions%20on%20the%20long-term%20deal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TANUJ%20LAKHINA%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Ffootball%2Ftop-stories%2Fwhy-isl-clubs-want-fancode-over-genius-sports-as-commercial-partner-explained%2Farticleshow%2F129864373.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20son%20and%20I%20built%20a%20successful%20bow%20tie%20business%20on%20Amazon%20together.%20We%20had%20to%20shut%20it%20down%20to%20save%20our%20relationship.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221296%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Andrea%20Henderson%20and%20her%20son%20on%20the%20beach%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c56f2048461c18d7be66d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22972%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20and%20her%20son%20started%20a%20business%20on%20Amazon.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Andrea%20Henderson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20noticing%20a%20bow%20tie%20trend%20at%20a%20wedding%2C%20my%20son%20and%20I%20launched%20an%20Amazon%20private%20label%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20business%20helped%20pay%20for%20Roland's%20tuition%20at%20a%20private%20HBCU%2C%20but%20we%20disagreed%20often.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20shut%20the%20business%20down%20because%20our%20relationship%20was%20worth%20more%20than%20the%20revenue.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20after%20a%20trip%20to%20Maine%20during%20my%20son's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-college-freshmen-successful-first-year-professor-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20year%20of%20college%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20attended%20his%20high%20school%20basketball%20coach's%20wedding%20and%20noticed%20that%20most%20of%20his%20teammates%20were%20wearing%20bow%20ties.%20We%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20trend%2C%20but%20we%20discovered%20something%20much%20bigger.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20and%20I%20started%20playing%20around%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20starting%20an%20online%20bow%20tie%20business.%20Roland%20liked%20the%20idea%20of%20being%20his%20own%20boss%2C%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-challenges-of-being-an-entrepreneur-from-loneliness-to-stress-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20an%20entrepreneur%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20liked%20the%20idea%20of%20building%20something%20for%20the%20family.%20I%20loved%20the%20idea%20of%20naming%20it%20after%20my%20father%20and%20my%20son%2C%20who%20share%20a%20name.%20I%20also%20liked%20the%20idea%20of%20having%20something%20to%20keep%20us%20connected%20while%20he%20was%20away%20at%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoland%20was%20the%20creative%20force.%20I%20was%20responsible%20for%20operations%20and%20logistics.%20He%20was%20away%20at%20college%2C%20but%20we%20made%20it%20work.%20We%20were%20excited%20to%20build%20a%20legacy%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e749a856-cbc5-48de-940e-6a04da94f56a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20figured%20out%20the%20formula%20fast%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20studying%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-amazonbasics-private-label-brands-7-22%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20private-label%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20learning%20about%20online%20traffic%20and%20keywords%2C%20we%20quickly%20mastered%20the%20process.%20It%20came%20at%20a%20great%20time.%20Roland%20had%20transferred%20from%20a%20junior%20college%20to%20a%20private%20four-year%20HBCU.%20It%20was%20an%20exciting%20move%2C%20but%20also%20very%20expensive%2C%20with%20tuition%2C%20fees%2C%20and%20room%20and%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20we%20thought%20we%20would%20be%20selling%20to%20young%2C%20swaggy%20college%20students%20and%20professors.%20Then%20someone%20asked%20if%20we%20could%20make%20one%20for%20her%20pig.%20Another%20person%20asked%20for%20a%20smaller%20size%20for%20a%20woman.%20We%20began%20looking%20at%20our%20data%20to%20learn%20who%20was%20actually%20buying.%20Our%20customer%20base%20was%20broad%20and%20far%20from%20what%20we%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20was%20doing%20well%2C%20and%20the%20money%20was%20going%20toward%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2Fhow-to-pay-for-college%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20expenses%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20being%20reinvested%20in%20growth.%20We%20explored%20different%20designs%20and%20complementary%20accessories%2C%20such%20as%20socks%20and%20pins.%20But%20the%20bestseller%20remained%20our%20bow%20ties.%20The%20winning%20formula%20was%20volume.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b9b48b4a-cfa3-4efb-8611-26238a347991%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThen%20the%20cracks%20started%20to%20show%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERoland%20began%20looking%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-fashion-week-best-celebrity-looks-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efashion%20week%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20selling%20in%20retail.%20He%20toyed%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20writing%20a%20book%20and%20creating%20a%20style%20guide.%20Social%20media%20was%20growing%2C%20and%20opportunities%20seemed%20plentiful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20breaking%20point%20came%20when%20Walmart%20approached%20us%20to%20sell%20on%20Walmart.com.%20Roland%20wanted%20to%20build%20a%20couture%20brand%20and%20sell%20on%20the%20runways%20of%20Fashion%20Week.%20I%20believed%20in%20the%20volume%20of%20a%20mass%20audience.%20We%20could%20not%20close%20that%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20him%20to%20be%20the%20face%20of%20the%20brand.%20He%20wanted%20to%20stay%20behind%20the%20scenes.%20I%20wanted%20to%20highlight%20one%20celebrity.%20He%20wanted%20to%20highlight%20another.%20Our%20differences%20were%20slowing%20us%20down.%20My%20son%20and%20I%20got%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-assistant-agent-in-meetings-etiquette-experts-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econference%20calls%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20disagreed%20in%20front%20of%20other%20people.%20It%20was%20awkward%20and%20uncomfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wanted%20more%20control%20of%20the%20money%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20prioritize%20tuition%20and%20business%20growth.%20Soon%20he%20was%20saying%20left%2C%20and%20I%20was%20saying%20right.%20The%20arguments%20got%20tedious%2C%20and%20we%20reached%20an%20impasse.%20The%20conversations%20were%20tense.%20Holidays%20were%20not%20fun.%20Everything%20became%20a%20potential%20powder%20keg%20for%20us%20and%20anyone%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227e8fb63f-f1b3-473b-af40-4f422ebe9e44%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20was%20never%20really%20about%20the%20business%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20surface%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20we%20disagreed%20about%20money%20and%20strategy%2C%20but%20below%20the%20surface%20was%20a%20mother%20who%20needed%20additional%20income%20to%20provide%20the%20college%20experience%20I%20wanted%20for%20him%2C%20and%20a%20son%20who%20was%20learning%20to%20flex%20his%20business%20skills%20and%20his%20adult%20independence.%20It%20was%20not%20just%20money%20for%20either%20of%20us.%20It%20was%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20check%20myself%2C%20especially%20after%20watching%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-succession-gets-right-about-real-life-billionaires-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSuccession%26quot%3B%20on%20HBO%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Was%20I%20becoming%20Logan%20Roy%2C%20the%20controlling%20parent%20who%20made%20his%20children%20feel%20unworthy%3F%20I%20also%20thought%20about%20%26quot%3BSoul%20Food%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20had%20aired%20years%20earlier.%20That%20show%20is%20about%20family%20bonds%20under%20strain%20and%20the%20terrifying%20realization%20that%20money%2C%20pride%2C%20and%20seemingly%20reasonable%20solutions%20can%20still%20tear%20apart%20what%20matters%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoland%20was%20trying%20to%20build%20an%20independent%20life%20while%20being%20shaped%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flived-with-grandparents-to-save-money-boundaries-changes-family-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20dynamics%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20expectations.%20The%20thing%20we%20had%20built%20to%20bring%20us%20closer%20was%20starting%20to%20tear%20us%20apart.%20So%2C%20while%20the%20business%20was%20profitable%2C%20I%20had%20to%20ask%20whether%20it%20was%20actually%20successful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245584c09-c4f6-4334-b220-a98a66b028a8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWalking%20away%20was%20the%20right%20call%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20asked%20why%20one%20of%20us%20could%20not%20simply%20run%20the%20business%20without%20the%20other.%20We%20contemplated%20that.%20But%20the%20deeper%20reality%20was%20about%20what%20the%20business%20had%20come%20to%20mean%20between%20us.%20Neither%20of%20us%20had%20the%20appetite%20to%20untangle%20it.%20It%20was%20easier%20to%20walk%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20can%20have%20fun%20now%3A%20at%20family%20dinners%2C%20on%20holidays%2C%20and%20on%20vacations.%20We%20now%20have%20priceless%20memories%20as%20mother%20and%20son%2C%20not%20co-founders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-son-built-s