%2Fyemens-houthis-join-iran-war-after-threats-launch-1st-missile-on-israel-11278295%23publisher%3Dnewsstand%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fyemens-houthis-join-iran-war-after-threats-launch-1st-missile-on-israel-11278295%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fyemens-houthis-join-iran-war-after-threats-launch-1st-missile-on-israel-11278295%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20nutrition%20scientist%20shared%203%20easy%20food%20swaps%20to%20make%20your%20meals%20heart-healthy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221651%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sarah%20Berry%20sits%20at%20a%20table.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6577bb87081653c9a67eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221238%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EProfessor%20Sarah%20Berry%20is%20a%20nutrition%20scientist%20who%20specializes%20in%20cardiovascular%20disease.%3Cp%3EZOE%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHeart%20disease%20is%20the%20leading%20cause%20of%20death%20in%20the%20US.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProfessor%20Sarah%20Berry%20said%20getting%20the%20basics%20right%20can%20make%20a%20huge%20difference%20to%20our%20heart%20health.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20of%20her%20tips%20was%20keeping%20the%20skin%20on%20potatoes%2C%20as%20it's%20a%20good%20source%20of%20fiber.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EHeart%20disease%20is%20the%20leading%20cause%20of%20death%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20but%20eating%20a%20nutritious%20diet%20can%20help%20reduce%20the%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutrition-researcher-eat-to-avoid-afternoon-crash-blood-sugar-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProfessor%20Sarah%20Berry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nutrition%20scientist%20who%20specializes%20in%20cardiovascular%20disease%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20nailing%20the%20basics%2C%20for%20example%20eating%20plenty%20of%20whole%20foods%20and%20avoiding%20refined%20sugar%2C%20is%20most%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20I've%20learned%20in%20my%2025%20years%20of%20nutrition%20research%20is%20that%20you%20shouldn't%20sweat%20the%20small%20stuff.%20And%20that%20if%20you%20get%20the%20basics%20right%2C%20you%20are%2095%25%20of%20the%20way%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20Berry%2C%20who%20is%20a%20professor%20at%20King's%20College%20London%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%202008%20meta-analysis%20published%20in%20the%20British%20Medical%20Journal%20found%20that%20following%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmediterranean-diet-best-healthy-eating-longevity-rankings-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMediterranean-style%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20filled%20with%20high-fiber%20fruit%20and%20veggies%2C%20healthy%20fats%2C%20lean%20proteins%2C%20and%20beans%2C%20could%20lower%20the%20risk%20of%20cardiovascular%20disease%20by%20up%20to%209%25%2C%20as%20well%20as%20decreasing%20the%20risk%20of%20several%20other%20chronic%20diseases%20including%20cancer%20and%20Alzheimer's%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20being%20said%2C%20it's%20also%20important%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20food%20is%20social%2C%20and%20it's%20difficult%20to%20change%20the%20way%20we%20eat.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20part%20of%20our%20culture%2C%20it's%20part%20of%20the%20environment%20we%20live%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20Berry%20said.%20That's%20why%20she%20recommends%20starting%20with%20some%20simple%20swaps%20that'll%20boost%20the%20nutrition%20profile%20of%20your%20meals%20without%20changing%20much%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f32f2398-d151-4f3e-9fea-73e9b08a37b7%5C%22%3ESwap%20white%20carbs%20for%20wholewheat%20versions%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20person%20has%20too%20much%20LDL%20cholesterol%20in%20their%20blood%2C%20it%20can%20form%20a%20sticky%20plaque%20in%20their%20arteries%2C%20putting%20them%20at%20greater%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheart-healthy-food-swaps-dietitian-studies-simple-habits-prevent-disease-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eheart%20disease%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Fiber%20can%20help%20keep%20%26quot%3Bbad%26quot%3B%20cholesterol%20at%20bay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESwapping%20refined%20carbs%20for%20their%20wholewheat%20counterparts%20is%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20eat%20more%20fiber%2C%20Berry%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20could%20buy%20rye%20bread%20instead%20of%20white%2C%20use%20brown%20or%20wild%20rice%20instead%20of%20jasmine%2C%20or%20whole%20wheat%20spaghetti%20instead%20of%20regular.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20switching%20entirely%20feels%20intimidating%2C%20you%20can%20start%20by%20replacing%20half%20of%20your%20portion%20of%20white%20rice%20with%20a%20wholewheat%20version%20for%20example%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20main%20thing%20is%20just%20enjoy%20your%20food%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268af7412-0dc9-4c13-be46-bff23e016d61%5C%22%3ESwap%20peeled%20potatoes%20for%20skin-on%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEating%20potatoes%20with%20the%20skin%20on%20is%20an%20easy%20way%20to%20increase%20the%20fiber%20content%20of%20your%20meal%20without%20changing%20the%20taste%2C%20Berry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20medium%20potato%20contains%20about%20two%20to%20three%20grams%20of%20fiber%2C%207%20to%2010%25%20of%20the%20daily%20recommended%20amount%2C%20but%20most%20of%20it%20comes%20from%20the%20skin%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Harvard%20T.H%20Chan%20School%20of%20Public%20Health's%20The%20Nutrition%20Score.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cece0a2f-5343-4f3a-9fc9-39b18705fb6f%5C%22%3ESwap%20meat%20for%20legumes%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBerry%20suggested%20adding%20some%20legumes%2C%20such%20as%20lentils%20or%20beans%2C%20to%20meat-based%20dishes.%20%26quot%3BYou%20take%20some%20of%20the%20meat%20out%20and%20you%20add%20pulses%20or%20beans%20so%20that%20you're%20still%20getting%20the%20meat%20that%20you%20want%2C%20but%20you%20are%20also%20adding%20some%20healthy%20fiber%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fred-meat-intake-type-2-diabetes-risk-linked-harvard-study-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ered%20and%20processed%20meat%3C%2Fa%3E%20regularly%20is%20consistently%20linked%20to%20a%20greater%20risk%20of%20heart%20disease%2C%20while%20plant-based%20diets%2C%20which%20are%20higher%20in%20fiber%2C%20have%20been%20found%20to%20boost%20heart%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202023%20study%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20JAMA%20Network%20Open%2C%2022%20pairs%20of%20identical%20twins%20were%20assigned%20either%20a%20vegan%20or%20an%20omnivorous%20diet%20for%20eight%20weeks.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20study%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fomnivore-vs-vegan-diet-vegan-lost-more-weight-lower-cholesterol-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evegan%20twins%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20lower%20LDL%20cholesterol%20and%20insulin%20levels%2C%20and%20had%20lost%20more%20weight%2C%20another%20risk%20factor%20for%20cardiovascular%20disease%2C%20according%20to%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutrition-scientist-shared-food-swaps-heart-healthy-meals-cardiovascular-disease-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774693741000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6577bb87081653c9a67eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnutrition-scientist-shared-food-swaps-heart-healthy-meals-cardiovascular-disease-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Professor%20Sarah%20Berry%2C%20a%20nutrition%20scientist%20who%20specializes%20in%20cardiovascular%20disease%2C%20said%20getting%20the%20basics%20right%20can%20go%20a%20long%20way%20toward%20supporting%20our%20heart%20health.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kschewitz%40bu