ey're%20long-distance%3B%20She's%20in%20Columbus%2C%20Ohio%2C%20and%20he's%20in%20Akron.%20When%20they're%20together%2C%20he%20said%20that%20he'll%20%26quot%3Btemper%26quot%3B%20his%20vibe%20coding.%20When%20they're%20on%20FaceTime%2C%20she'll%20sometimes%20spot%20him%20typing%20off%20to%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECouples%20like%20Deagan%20and%20Kemelgor%20exist%20across%20the%20country.%20One%20partner%20is%20enthralled%20by%20the%20changes%20in%20AI%20code%20editors%20and%20stays%20up%20late%20with%20them.%20The%20other%20couldn't%20tell%20Cursor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenais-codex-lead-shares-tips-engineers-stand-out-email-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efrom%20Codex%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20all%20relationships%20have%20differing%20interests.%20Kemelgor%20likes%20painting%20handbags%20and%20watching%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freality-tv-bravo-real-housewives-rhoslc-helped-connect-adult-daughter-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EThe%20Real%20Housewives%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3B%20Deagan%20supports%20from%20afar.%20Vibe%20coding%20is%20exposing%20a%20level%20of%20enthusiasm%20that%20some%20couples%20have%20found%20difficult%20to%20contain%2C%20though.%20One%20told%20me%20that%20they%20had%20to%20set%20boundaries%2C%20like%20not%20using%20Claude%20Code%20while%20the%20kids%20are%20awake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20coding%20revolution%20is%20here.%20Now%2C%20you've%20got%20to%20explain%20it%20to%20your%20spouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e96c8d4-35d8-41bd-b50e-8f47c8f18e46%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELoving%20the%20vibe%20coder%20in%20your%20life%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKendra%20Ramirez%20often%20finds%20herself%20up%20past%20midnight%20with%20Claude%20Code.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20night%20before%20our%20call%2C%20the%2052-year-old%20Cincinnati%20resident%20vibe%20coded%20until%2012%3A30%20a.m.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20such%20a%20nerd%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20digital%20agency%20owner%20said.%20Ramirez%20is%20an%20%26quot%3Bideas%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20multiple%20times%3B%20to%20see%20those%20ideas%20come%20to%20life%20is%20thrilling%2C%20and%20she%20has%20to%20keep%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20husband%2C%20Jeff%20Fein%2C%20works%20in%20commercial%20construction%20and%20doesn't%20own%20a%20laptop.%20%26quot%3BThe%20man%20had%20a%20flip%20phone%20for%20many%2C%20many%20years%20past%20flip%20phone%20stage%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Ramirez%20is%20excited%20about%20her%20work%2C%20she'll%20run%20up%20to%20Fein%20and%20show%20it%20off.%20He'll%20respond%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20that's%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20told%20him%20this%20past%20week%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20would%20like%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20than%20'That's%20good.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERamirez%20has%20learned%20to%20bring%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineers-on-vibe-coding-ai-tools-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evibe-coded%20projects%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20her%20AI-loving%20friends%20instead.%20She%20also%20gets%20that%20Fein%20has%20his%20own%20passions%2C%20like%20concrete%20work%2C%20that%20she's%20not%20interested%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jeff%20Fein%20and%20Kendra%20Ramirez%20are%20pictured.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6a5c18e44c01630d3177e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKendra%20Ramirez%20loves%20to%20vibe%20code.%20Her%20husband%20doesn't%20own%20a%20laptop.%3Cp%3EKendra%20Ramirez%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20vibe%20coders%20that%20I%20spoke%20to%20told%20me%20that%2C%20once%20they%20started%2C%20it%20was%20difficult%20to%20stop.%20Aaron%20Perkins%20compared%20it%20to%20the%20joy%20of%20playing%20video%20games%20like%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frichard-garriott-interview-2011-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUltima%20Online%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BEverQuest%26quot%3B%20in%20college.%20The%2043-year-old%20entrepreneur%20also%20said%20he%20has%20severe%20ADHD%20and%20that%20vibe%20coding%20keeps%20him%20engaged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerkins%20met%20his%20wife%2C%20Patricia%20Perkins%2C%20in%20college.%20They've%20been%20married%20for%2020%20years%20and%20live%20together%20in%20Anniston%2C%20Alabama.%20Sometimes%20he'll%20show%20her%20the%20projects.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20I'm%20speaking%20a%20different%20language%20a%20lot%20of%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatricia%20Perkins%2C%20a%2041-year-old%20stay-at-home%20mom%2C%20described%20her%20response%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bsmile%20and%20nod.%26quot%3B%20She%20often%20finds%20her%20husband%20staying%20up%20late%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-creator-three-principles-boris-cherny-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewith%20Claude%20Code%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He'll%20stay%20at%20the%20computer%20until%2011%3A30%20p.m.%2C%20compared%20to%20her%209%3A30%20p.m.%20bedtime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20late%20hours%20don't%20bother%20her.%20He%20helps%20out%20around%20the%20house%2C%20so%20she%20sees%20staying%20up%20to%20do%20his%20own%20thing%20as%20a%20fine%20tradeoff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersonally%2C%20she%20finds%20AI%20%26quot%3Bsci-fi%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbizarro.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20always%20totally%20immersed%20in%20mom%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Patricia%20Perkins%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20time%20to%20talk%20to%20myself%2C%20much%20less%20an%20AI%20agent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe'd%20rather%20talk%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eabout%20health%20and%20the%20human%20body.%20When%20she%20shares%20her%20medications%20and%20foods%2C%20Aaron%20Perkins%20responds%20with%20the%20same%20smile%20and%20nod.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Patricia%20and%20Aaron%20Perkins%20are%20pictured.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6a5e7445048b5f68bbab6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221407%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPatricia%20Perkins%20will%20%26quot%3Bsmile%20and%20nod%26quot%3B%20when%20her%20husband%2C%20Aaron%20Perkins%2C%20describes%20his%20vibe%20coding.%3Cp%3EAaron%20Perkins%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0e9233a-22ed-401b-90e7-017c86312eb1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20much%20Claude%20is%20too%20much%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETodd%20Ponsky%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Diana%20Ponsky%2C%20set%20a%20rule%3A%20no%20vibe%20coding%20while%20the%20kids%20are%20awake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2053-year-old%20pediatric%20surgeon%20from%20Cleveland%20loves%20to%20build.%20He%20made%20a%20medical%20scenario%20simulation%20for%20doctors%20and%20an%20automatic%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20updater.%20He%20also%20made%20an%20app%20that%20transcribes%20the%20short-form%20videos%20he%20likes%20and%20makes%20them%20searchable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20can%20keep%20him%20up%20late.%20He%20calls%20this%20the%20%26quot%3Balmost%20there%26quot%3B%20problem%3A%20some%20initial%20prompts%20will%20make%20a%20solid%20project%2C%20but%20then%20you%20can%20spend%20hours%20tweaking%20and%20perfecting%20it.%20%26quot%3BI%20had%20to%20put%20in%20my%20own%20guardrails%2C%20because%20it%20was%20becoming%20an%20addiction%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20tells%20her%20he's%20building%20something%20new%2C%20she%20rolls%20her%20eyes.%20They've%20agreed%20that%20he%20will%20vibe%20code%20only%20when%20the%20kids%20are%20sleeping%20or%20out%20of%20the%20house.%20The%20kids%20shouldn't%20see%20him%20on%20the%20computer%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20dig%20into%20family%2C%20it%20was%20going%20into%20sleeping%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227301%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Diana%20and%20Todd%20Ponsky%20are%20pictured.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6a58d445048b5f68bbab1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224867%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETodd%20Ponsky%20said%20he%20had%20to%20put%20up%20%26quot%3Bguardrails%26quot%3B%20on%20his%20vibe%20coding.%3Cp%3ETodd%20Ponsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EVibe%20coding%20can%20be%20a%20time%20suck%2C%20devouring%20the%20hours%20of%20the%20day%20that%20one%20might%20want%20to%20spend%20with%20their%20partner%20or%20children.%20(In%20that%20way%2C%20it's%20no%20different%20from%20bingeing%20TV%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fdoomscrolling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edoom-scrolling%20on%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E.)%20Some%20couples%20are%20building%20rules%20to%20make%20sure%20love%20and%20Claude%20don't%20fight%20for%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJanette%20Camacho%2C%20a%2053-year-old%20edtech%20consultant%20from%20Palm%20Beach%2C%20Florida%2C%20doesn't%20have%20to%20worry%20about%20that%20now.%20She's%20upped%20her%20Claude%20subscription%20to%20the%20%24200-a-month%20plan%20and%20has%20bots%20that%20can%20operate%20autonomously%20throughout%20the%20night.%20Her%20husband%2C%20who%20works%20in%20law%20enforcement%20and%20doesn't%20care%20much%20about%20AI%2C%20often%20says%20that%20her%20bots%20are%20her%20%26quot%3Bboyfriend.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20remembered%20one%20February%20trip%20when%20she%20was%20on%20the%20more%20limited%20%2420-a-month%20Claude%20plan.%20She%20was%20visiting%20her%20daughters%20%E2%80%94%20one%20in%20Virginia%2C%20the%20other%20in%20Nashville%20%E2%80%94%20and%20had%20to%20bring%20her%20laptop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClaude%20would%20tell%20her%3A%20%26quot%3BYour%20next%20available%20open%20slot%20is%20going%20to%20be%20at%202%2C%26quot%3B%20Camacho%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20like%2C%20'At%202%2C%20I%20need%20to%20open%20my%20computer.'%20That's%20exactly%20what%20I%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couples%20I%20spoke%20to%20were%20all%20looking%20to%20find%20balance%20together.%20When%20Kemelgor%20posted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40relovedbyleslie%2Fvideo%2F7617530863110196493%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20her%20boyfriend's%20hours%20vibe%20coding%2C%20she%20and%20Deagan%20watched%20the%20comments%20flood%20with%20complaints%20about%20how%20Claude%20was%20the%20other%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20so%20nice%20to%20have%20a%20partner%20that%20recognizes%20and%20supports%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Deagan%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20thankful%20for%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-gap-relationship-vibe-code-couples-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774691161000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6a69e8e44c01630d31783%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-gap-relationship-vibe-code-couples-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20%26quot%3BClaude-gap%26quot%3B%20relationship%20is%20on%20the%20rise.%20Vibe%20coders%20told%20Business%20Insider%20about%20trying%20to%20explain%20their%20late-night%20sessions%20to%20their%20spouses.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hchandonnet%40insider.com%20(Henry%20Chandonnet)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclaude-gap-relationship-vibe-code-couples-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22When%20my%20job%20started%20feeling%20like%20being%20with%20a%20bad%20boyfriend%2C%20I%20knew%20I%20had%20to%20quit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223598%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lisa%20Fail%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6b792e99557fb1b08a0b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222699%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELisa%20Fail%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20career%20break%20after%20experiencing%20a%20%26quot%3Bbad%20boyfriend%26quot%3B%20moment%20with%20her%20relationship%20to%20work.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Lisa%20Fail%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELisa%20Fail%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20career%20break%20after%20about%20three%20decades%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20frank%20conversation%20with%20her%20boss%20signaled%20she%20was%20putting%20in%20more%20than%20she%20was%20getting%20back.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BI%20felt%20duped%20by%20my%20own%20illusion%2C%26quot%3B%20Fail%2C%2061%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Lisa%20Fail%2C%2061%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20Durham%2C%20North%20Carolina.%20In%20late%202024%2C%20after%20about%20three%20decades%20in%20tech%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20career%20break.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20brevity%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20super%20lucky.%20I've%20really%20loved%20every%20job%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20not%20when%20I%20was%20a%20teenager%20working%20at%20McDonald's%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20rest%20of%20them%20have%20been%20amazing.%20Good%20people%2C%20fun%20work.%20Not%20everyone%20has%20had%20that%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20choice%20to%20step%20back%20came%20about%20two%20years%20before%20I%20left.%20Work%20was%20always%20my%20thing.%20I%20have%20a%20husband%20and%20two%20kids.%20They're%20amazing%2C%20yet%20work%20was%20where%20I%20put%20a%20lot%20of%20energy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%2C%20I%20said%20to%20my%20boss%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20looking%20for%20something%20else.%20What's%20next%20for%20me%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I%20realized%20at%20a%20certain%20age%20I%20was%20never%20going%20to%20be%20CEO.%26quot%3B%20It%20became%20clear%20he%20thought%20I'd%20reached%20my%20peak%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22db6b0a65-c176-4452-bf74-ad4a3d03aa7d%5C%22%3EDuped%20by%20my%20own%20illusion%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20drove%20home%20that%20evening%2C%20I%20reflected%20on%20the%20conversation.%20It%20was%20the%20bad-boyfriend%20moment%3A%20You%20realize%20you're%20putting%20everything%20into%20it%2C%20and%20there's%20not%20really%20any%20commitment%20on%20the%20other%20side.%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20figure%20something%20out%2C%20because%20this%20feels%20like%20rejection.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20been%20doing%20cybersecurity%20work%2C%20and%20it%20was%20super%20fun.%20I%20had%20this%20secret%20hope%20that%20eventually%20I%20would%20be%20recognized%20or%20promoted.%20My%20boss%20was%20being%20honest%20with%20me%20%E2%80%94%20and%20ultimately%20commiserating%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it%20was%20really%20disappointing%20to%20hear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20felt%20duped%20by%20my%20own%20illusion.%20I%20wasn't%20perceptive%20enough%20to%20see%20that%20I%20didn't%20have%20much%20room%20to%20move%20up%2C%20because%20I%20liked%20the%20work%20and%20was%20focused%20on%20getting%20it%20done.%20I%20was%20the%20annoying%20coworker%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%20guys%2C%20happy%20Monday.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20that%20conversation%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20become%20a%20bit%20more%20mercenary%20about%20it%2C%20which%20sounds%20terrible.%20But%20if%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20transactional%2C%20let's%20make%20it%20transactional.%20So%20I%20stopped%20volunteering%20for%20everything%20and%20getting%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20everything.%20I%20kept%20working%20very%20hard%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%2060%20hours%20a%20week%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20prepared%20for%20that%2C%20because%20suddenly%20I%20wasn't%20putting%20my%20whole%20self%20into%20it%20and%20was%20still%20getting%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20money%20back.%20But%20it%20didn't%20feel%20as%20good%3B%20it%20felt%20hollow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20I%20worked%20as%20hard%20%E2%80%94%20but%20part-time%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20that's%20the%20answer.%26quot%3B%20By%20then%2C%20I%20had%20a%20different%20boss%2C%20and%20she%20was%20willing%20to%20try%20that%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20fun%20at%20first%2C%20but%20after%20a%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20spending%20my%20time%20at%20my%20desk%2C%20and%20life%20was%20passing%20me%20by.%20After%20pulling%20back%2C%20I%20never%20could%20fall%20in%20love%20with%20it%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBest%20case%2C%20I've%20got%20maybe%2020%20years%20of%20great%20health%20left.%20That's%20like%207%2C000%20days.%20That's%201%2C000%20weeks%20%E2%80%94%201%2C000%20Mondays.%20That's%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22931335b9-3d7a-4d42-b3cf-f939fd52f295%5C%22%3EOne%20hand%20on%20my%20phone%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20leave%20a%20job%2C%20it's%20kind%20of%20like%20a%20retrospective%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20project.%20Looking%20back%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhoa.%20How%20many%20vacations%20did%20I%20drag%20my%20computer%20on%3F%20How%20many%20times%20was%20I%20shushing%20my%20family%20in%20the%20background%2C%20or%20sneaking%20off%20to%20a%20closet%20in%20the%20Vrbo%20for%20a%20conference%20call%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20weren't%20things%20that%20I%20missed%2C%20but%20things%20that%20I%20hadn't%20fully%20participated%20in%20because%20I%20had%20one%20hand%20on%20my%20phone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20always%20felt%20so%20time-impoverished.%20I%20would%20cook%20dinner%20and%20be%20working%20on%20whatever%2C%20or%20get%20in%20the%20shower%2C%20put%20my%20phone%20down%2C%20get%20out%2C%20and%20check%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuddenly%2C%20after%20leaving%2C%20I%20was%20overwhelmed.%20My%20time%20is%20not%20constrained.%20I'm%20not%20going%20to%20live%20forever%2C%20but%20today%20is%20mine.%20What%20am%20I%20going%20to%20do%3F%20I'm%20going%20to%20go%20do%20some%20yoga.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20like%20it's%20a%20break%2C%20not%20retirement.%20I%20have%20no%20desire%20to%20go%20back%20to%20corporate%2C%20and%20particularly%20not%20tech.%20I've%20been%20there%2C%20and%20it%20was%20great.%20When%20I%20go%20back%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20something%20that%20I%20can%20love%20and%20be%20completely%20enmeshed%20in%20%E2%80%94%20when%20you%20look%20up%2C%20you're%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20it's%20dark%20again.%26quot%3B%20Maybe%20something%20nonprofit%2C%20maybe%20government%2C%20maybe%20a%20startup.%20It's%20definitely%20the%20sense%20of%20purpose%20and%20greater%20good%20beyond%20stockholders%20and%20CEOs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMan%2C%20this%20is%20easily%20top%20five%2C%20maybe%20top%20three%20best%20decision%20I've%20ever%20made.%20Could%20I%20have%20made%20it%20sooner%3F%20Maybe%2C%20but%20it%20was%20just%20about%20the%20right%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bc3ee9a5-a000-48c3-b22e-a3f62f0662eb%5C%22%3EYour%20real%20business%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20get%20up%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20I%20think%20if%20I%20were%20not%20here%20today%20%E2%80%94%20drinking%20my%20coffee%2C%20reading%20the%20news%20%E2%80%94%20I'd%20be%20scurrying%20back%20in%20my%20pajamas%20and%20slippers%2C%20trying%20to%20get%20caught%20up%20on%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20miss%20the%20%26quot%3BWhat%20did%20I%20miss%3F%20What%20did%20they%20find%20overnight%3F%20Is%20there%20anything%20that's%20going%20to%20stop%20our%20deployment%3F%26quot%3B%20It's%20all%20of%20that%20false%20urgency.%20Now%2C%20it's%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20no.%20We're%20almost%20out%20of%20half-and-half.%26quot%3B%20That's%20the%20urgency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWork%20is%20not%20your%20life.%20Your%20employer%20only%20buys%2040%20hours.%20Every%20hour%20they%20do%20not%20pay%20for%20is%20yours.%20Enjoy%20your%20work%20%E2%80%94%20love%20your%20work%20%E2%80%94%20but%20know%20your%20real%20business%20is%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20your%20career%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Atparadis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etparadis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-worker-shares-why-she-took-career-break-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1774691102000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6b6d38e44c01630d3182a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-worker-shares-why-she-took-career-break-2026-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20tech%20veteran%20decided%20to%20take%20a%20career%20break%20after%20realizing%20she%20was%20putting%20into%20her%20job%20than%20she%20was%20getting%20back.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-worker-shares-why-she-took-career-break-2026-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20founder%20uses%20AI%20as%20a%20'CFO'%20during%20tax%20season.%20His%20CPA%20still%20gets%20the%20final%20say.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22kyle%20ray%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69c6bff8445048b5f68bbbc6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKyle%20Ray%20is%20the%20founder%20of%20Geek%20Window%20Cleaning.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Kyle%20Ray%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKyle%20Ray%20is%20using%20various%20AI%20tools%20to%20scale%20his%20window%20cleaning%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20tax%20season%2C%20he's%20using%20ChatGPT%20to%20find%20strategies%20that%20could%20save%20him%20money.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20also%20uses%20it%20to%20help%20him%20prepare%20for%20conversations%20with%20his%20CPA.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESmall%20business%20owner%20Kyle%20Ray%20doesn't%20have%20the%20budget%20to%20hire%20a%20full%20C-suite.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBasically%20my%20entire%20leadership%20team%20is%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Geek%20Window%20Cleaning%20founder%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20a%20massive%20company%2C%20so%20I%20can't%20afford%20the%20salaries%20for%20those%20kinds%20of%20people.%20But%20I%20can%20pay%2040%20bucks%20a%20month%20for%20Claude%20and%20ChatGPT.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20tax%20season%20in%20particular%2C%20he's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-one-business-owner-is-leveraging-ai-to-grow-company-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleaning%20into%20AI's%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20using%20what%20he%20calls%20his%20%26quot%3BAI%20CFO%26quot%3B%20despite%20having%20a%20CPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERay%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbartender-turned-window-cleaning-side-hustle-into-six-figure-business-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egrew%20Geek%20from%20a%20side%20hustle%20to%20a%20six-figure%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20uses%20a%20handful%20of%20AI%20and%20software%20tools.%20For%20tax%20questions%2C%20though%2C%20he%20turns%20to%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20he%20asks%20it%20to%20surface%20tax%20strategies%20that%20could%20save%20him%20money.%20He%20said%20AI%20helped%20him%20think%20through%20whether%20some%20sales%20reps%20could%20qualify%20as%20independent%20contractors%20rather%20than%20W-2%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnytime%20you're%20a%20business%20owner%2C%20you're%20like%2C%20'Can%20this%20person%20be%20a%201099%20contractor%2C%20or%20do%20they%20have%20to%20be%20a%20W-2%20employee%3F'%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%20He%20said%20that%20structure%20can%20be%20more%20favorable%20from%20a%20tax%20perspective%20because%20employers%20generally%20don't%20owe%20the%20same%20payroll%20taxes%20on%20contractors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20uses%20AI%20to%20help%20him%20prepare%20for%20conversations%20with%20his%20CPA.%20One%20of%20his%20favorite%20questions%20for%20ChatGPT%20is%3A%20%26quot%3BWhat%20questions%20am%20I%20not%20asking%20that%20I%20should%20be%20asking%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20using%20it%20to%20double-check%20what%20he's%20paying%20for%2C%20too.%20Ray%20said%20he'll%20prepare%20his%20own%20taxes%20using%20ChatGPT%20as%20an%20assistant%2C%20then%20compare%20those%20results%20with%20what%20his%20accountant%20produces.%20From%20there%2C%20he%20brings%20any%20discrepancies%20or%20new%20ideas%20back%20to%20his%20CPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20they'll%20be%20like%2C%20'Oh%20yeah%2C%20I%20didn't%20catch%20that%2C'%20or%2C%20'Oh%2C%20you're%20right.%20You%20can%20do%20that.'%20Or%20they'll%20say%2C%20'No%2C%20you%20can't%20do%20that%20because%20x%2C%20y%2C%20z%2C'%26quot%3B%20Ray%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20just%20a%20good%20way%20to%20inspect%20what%20you%20expect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20benefits%20of%20working%20with%20AI%20tools%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20accessibility.%20Rather%20than%20having%20to%20schedule%20and%20prepare%20for%20a%20call%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20available%20whenever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20his%20CPA%20gets%20the%20final%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20trust%20it%20110%25%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20AI.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20always%20have%20someone%20look%20it%20over.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20especially%20true%20when%20AI%20moves%20from%20explaining%20tax%20concepts%20to%20offering%20advice%20tailored%20to%20a%20specific%20business%2C%20CPA%20Amanda%20Han%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20can%20be%20especially%20helpful%20for%20explaining%20basic%20concepts%2C%20such%20as%20what%20depreciation%20is%20or%20how%20an%20S%20corp%20works%2C%20she%20said.%20However%2C%20if%20you're%20asking%2C%20%26quot%3BIs%20an%20S%20corporation%20good%20for%20me%3F%20That's%20probably%20still%20a%20question%20for%20a%20CPA%20rather%20than%20AI.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHan%20said%20she%20and%20other%20CPAs%20use%20AI%20tools%20in%20their%20own%20practices.%20It%20can%20be%20useful%20for%20tasks%20like%20surfacing%20relevant%20court%20cases%2C%20she%20said%2C%20but%20it%20still%20falls%20short%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20applying%20that%20information%20to%20an%20individual%20client's%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUltimately%2C%20the%20applicability%20of%20a%20specific%20court%20case%20to%20a%20specific%20client%20is%20really%20the%20part%20that's%20not%20really%20there%20yet%20for%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat%20still%20needs%20a%20human%20touch.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHan%20said%20AI%20is%20best%20used%20for%20lower-stakes%20tasks%20that%20don't%20require%20much%20judgment%2C%20like%20organizing%20transactions%20or%20helping%20business%20owners%20draft%20questions%20for%20their%20CPA.%20But%20people%20shouldn't%20assume%20it's%20always%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDouble-check%2C%20and%20always%20use%20your%20own%20judgment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20if%20something%20sounds%20too%20good%20to%20be%20true%2C%20it%20probably%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Ray%2C%20AI's%20appeal%20goes%20beyond%20tax%20help%3A%20It's%20readily%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCPAs%20%E2%80%94%20their%20time%20is%20valuable%2C%20and%20during%20tax%20season%20is%20when%20they're%20the%20busiest%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20they%20have%20less%20time%20to%20sit%20there%20and%20just%20hold%20your%20hand.%20And%20ChatGPT%20will%20hold%20your%20hand%2024%2F7.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-for-taxes-small-business-owner-cpa-cfo-chatgpt-2026-3%5C%22%3EBusiness